subSubSection.paragraph:
Cell I ± globose, often heart-shaped (
Fig. 86A–B
). Primary appendage variably branched. Cell III barrel-shaped, longer than broad, usually broadened distally, with a darkened outer margin. Usually four secondary appendages for each antheridium. Each antheridium with eight phialides. [Detailed descriptions: 
Thaxter 1908
; 
Majewski 1988
, 
1994b
; 
Santamaria 1989
]
